\": \"the produce\", \"from\": 1560, \"to\": 1571}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is different numbers floating around depending on who you talk to, but we do not have that baseline,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 1616, \"to\": 1734, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"different numbers\", \"from\": 1626, \"to\": 1643}, {\"ngram\": \"that baseline\", \"from\": 1709, \"to\": 1722}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even if a baseline is determined, meeting the ambitious goal will be an uphill battle.\", \"from\": 1736, \"to\": 1822, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a baseline\", \"from\": 1744, \"to\": 1754}, {\"ngram\": \"the ambitious goal\", \"from\": 1778, \"to\": 1796}, {\"ngram\": \"an uphill battle\", \"from\": 1805, \"to\": 1821}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A 2016 report by Foodprint Melbourne estimated that the Melbourne food bowlhad the capacity to produce41% of the city's total food needs.\", \"from\": 1824, \"to\": 1961, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1851, \"end\": 1860, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\", \"score\": 0.9999983575030302, \"rank\": 1.52951979539703e-06, \"text\": \"Melbourne\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\"}, {\"begin\": 1880, \"end\": 1889, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\", \"score\": 0.9999983575030302, \"rank\": 1.52951979539703e-06, \"text\": \"Melbourne\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A 2016 report\", \"from\": 1824, \"to\": 1837}, {\"ngram\": \"the capacity\", \"from\": 1903, \"to\": 1915}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's total food needs\", \"from\": 1933, \"to\": 1960}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But that land is shrinking.\", \"from\": 1962, \"to\": 1989, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that land\", \"from\": 1966, \"to\": 1975}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By 2040, the report predicted, the fertile plains would produce just 18% of the city's food needsasprime agricultural land is consumed by the construction of sprawling housing estates.\", \"from\": 1990, \"to\": 2174, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the report\", \"from\": 1999, \"to\": 2009}, {\"ngram\": \"the fertile plains\", \"from\": 2021, \"to\": 2039}, {\"ngram\": \"just 18%\", \"from\": 2054, \"to\": 2062}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's food needsasprime agricultural land\", \"from\": 2066, \"to\": 2112}, {\"ngram\": \"the construction\", \"from\": 2128, \"to\": 2144}, {\"ngram\": \"housing estates\", \"from\": 2158, \"to\": 2173}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's very concerning, there is good reasons why we want to be growing food around cities in the future,\\\" the report's lead author, Dr Rachel Carey, said.\", \"from\": 2176, \"to\": 2330, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2311, \"end\": 2317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachel_Green\", \"score\": 0.9753006481816928, \"rank\": 0.019319113874073857, \"text\": \"Rachel\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachel_Green\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachel_Green\"}, {\"begin\": 2318, \"end\": 2323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariah_Carey\", \"score\": 0.9246992114370657, \"rank\": 0.08143273794428518, \"text\": \"Carey\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariah_Carey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariah_Carey\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"good reasons\", \"from\": 2208, \"to\": 2220}, {\"ngram\": \"food\", \"from\": 2247, \"to\": 2251}, {\"ngram\": \"cities\", \"from\": 2259, \"to\": 2265}, {\"ngram\": \"the future\", \"from\": 2269, \"to\": 2279}, {\"ngram\": \"the report's lead author\", \"from\": 2282, \"to\": 2306}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sydney is faring even worse.Another studyfound the farmland remaining around the city is only capable of meeting20% of the city's overall food needs, with more losses expected if urban sprawl continues unabated.\", \"from\": 2332, \"to\": 2543, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2332, \"end\": 2338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9995962451745991, \"rank\": 0.00040376529234705726, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Another\", \"from\": 2360, \"to\": 2367}, {\"ngram\": \"the farmland\", \"from\": 2379, \"to\": 2391}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 2409, \"to\": 2417}, {\"ngram\": \"meeting20%\", \"from\": 2437, \"to\": 2447}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's overall food needs\", \"from\": 2451, \"to\": 2480}, {\"ngram\": \"more losses\", \"from\": 2487, \"to\": 2498}, {\"ngram\": \"urban sprawl\", \"from\": 2511, \"to\": 2523}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Sydney is kind of where Melbourne could be heading if we do not change our policies,\\\" Carey said.\", \"from\": 2544, \"to\": 2642, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2545, \"end\": 2551, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9995962451745991, \"rank\": 0.00040376529234705726, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}, {\"begin\": 2569, \"end\": 2578, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\", \"score\": 0.9999983575030302, \"rank\": 1.52951979539703e-06, \"text\": \"Melbourne\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\"}, {\"begin\": 2631, \"end\": 2636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariah_Carey\", \"score\": 0.9246992114370657, \"rank\": 0.08143273794428518, \"text\": \"Carey\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariah_Carey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariah_Carey\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our policies\", \"from\": 2616, \"to\": 2628}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sign up toThe Rural Network Subscribe to Calla Wahlquist's fortnightly update on Australian rural and regional affairs after newsletter promotion Last year, aNew South Wales inquiry into food production and supplyfound productive agricultural land in peri-urban areas was under increasing threat from development.\", \"from\": 2644, \"to\": 2960, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2726, \"end\": 2736, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"score\": 0.9943524785633291, \"rank\": 0.005676225205184119, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\"}, {\"begin\": 2815, \"end\": 2820, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Wales\", \"score\": 0.7262813948241769, \"rank\": 0.3768767960811602, \"text\": \"Wales\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Wales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Wales\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"toThe Rural Network Subscribe\", \"from\": 2652, \"to\": 2681}, {\"ngram\": \"Calla Wahlquist's fortnightly update\", \"from\": 2685, \"to\": 2721}, {\"ngram\": \"newsletter promotion\", \"from\": 2769, \"to\": 2789}, {\"ngram\": \"food production\", \"from\": 2831, \"to\": 2846}, {\"ngram\": \"supplyfound productive agricultural land\", \"from\": 2851, \"to\": 2891}, {\"ngram\": \"peri-urban areas\", \"from\": 2895, \"to\": 2911}, {\"ngram\": \"increasing threat\", \"from\": 2922, \"to\": 2939}, {\"ngram\": \"development\", \"from\": 2945, \"to\": 2956}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Afederal inquiryhad similar findings, recommending the protection of agricultural land from urban sprawl.\", \"from\": 2962, \"to\": 3067, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Afederal\", \"from\": 2962, \"to\": 2970}, {\"ngram\": \"similar findings\", \"from\": 2982, \"to\": 2998}, {\"ngram\": \"the protection\", \"from\": 3013, \"to\": 3027}, {\"ngram\": \"agricultural land\", \"from\": 3031, \"to\": 3048}, {\"ngram\": \"urban sprawl\", \"from\": 3054, \"to\": 3066}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It recommended the governmentascertain the optimal location of food distribution centres and develop a national food supply chain map to better understand the journey of food from paddock to plate.\", \"from\": 3068, \"to\": 3265, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the governmentascertain\", \"from\": 3083, \"to\": 3106}, {\"ngram\": \"the optimal location\", \"from\": 3107, \"to\": 3127}, {\"ngram\": \"food distribution centres\", \"from\": 3131, \"to\": 3156}, {\"ngram\": \"a national food supply chain map\", \"from\": 3169, \"to\": 3201}, {\"ngram\": \"the journey\", \"from\": 3223, \"to\": 3234}, {\"ngram\": \"food\", \"from\": 3238, \"to\": 3242}, {\"ngram\": \"paddock\", \"from\": 3248, \"to\": 3255}, {\"ngram\": \"plate\", \"from\": 3259, \"to\": 3264}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Associate Prof Andrea Gaynor, an environmental historian from the University of Western Australia, said that while there are benefits to locally-grown food, it can still be vulnerable to supply chain shocks.\", \"from\": 3267, \"to\": 3474, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3267, \"end\": 3281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associate_professor\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Associate Prof\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associate_professor\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associate_professor\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an environmental historian\", \"from\": 3297, \"to\": 3323}, {\"ngram\": \"the University\", \"from\": 3329, \"to\": 3343}, {\"ngram\": \"Western Australia\", \"from\": 3347, \"to\": 3364}, {\"ngram\": \"benefits\", \"from\": 3392, \"to\": 3400}, {\"ngram\": \"locally-grown food\", \"from\": 3404, \"to\": 3422}, {\"ngram\": \"chain shocks\", \"from\": 3461, \"to\": 3473}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think the idea of bringing agriculture closer to the city is about making it smaller scale, adaptive andcommunity focused agriculture,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 3476, \"to\": 3624, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the idea\", \"from\": 3485, \"to\": 3493}, {\"ngram\": \"agriculture\", \"from\": 3506, \"to\": 3517}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 3528, \"to\": 3536}, {\"ngram\": \"adaptive andcommunity\", \"from\": 3571, \"to\": 3592}, {\"ngram\": \"agriculture\", \"from\": 3601, \"to\": 3612}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That gives children the chance to see how food can be grown, for urban wastes to be used, it can encourage circular economy type behaviours and reduce waste.\\\"\", \"from\": 3625, \"to\": 3784, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"children\", \"from\": 3637, \"to\": 3645}, {\"ngram\": \"the chance\", \"from\": 3646, \"to\": 3656}, {\"ngram\": \"food\", \"from\": 3668, \"to\": 3672}, {\"ngram\": \"urban wastes\", \"from\": 3691, \"to\": 3703}, {\"ngram\": \"circular economy type behaviours\", \"from\": 3733, \"to\": 3765}, {\"ngram\": \"waste\", \"from\": 3777, \"to\": 3782}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gaynor said colonial Australia had a long history of growing fruit and vegetable in or near cities, but after the second world war, those habits began to deteriorate as large-scalecommercial horticulture operations were developed and cities expanded.\", \"from\": 3786, \"to\": 4036, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3798, \"end\": 3816, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Australia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.3650869159203275e-35, \"text\": \"colonial Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Australia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Gayn